<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> All in all, the Lexx or a Vorlon Ship could beat the pants off of either. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Lexx's weapon is certainly powerful, and would cause problems for any Imperial ship it took a disliking to, yet it's damage absorbtion capabilities are sorely lacking. He has no shields, and minimal armor. But then, this could prove useful, as Imperial weapons would go right through him, transferring only minimal energy. Unless they flakburst, in which case Lexx is dead. Vorlon ships, while having superior defensive capabilites than Lexx, are much weaker offensively. Compared to post-ICS Imperial ships, they are pitiful.<br>
